column3: Ghimthota wishes to entrust you with an important task.

Among the possessions of Ahtzapfyn, the pirate behind the attempted destruction of the <Emphasis>Victory</Emphasis>, was found a missive written in some manner of code. Unable to find anyone to decipher the curious lettering, Ghimthota wishes to enlist the help of Baderon and his irregular group of contacts. Deliver the missive to the proprietor of the Drowning Wench.

After perusing the contents of the missive, Baderon is visibly distressed. It appears the message was, indeed, of vital importance, though you have yet to learn the exact nature of the threat contained therein. Prepare yourself for the worst eventuality, and speak with Baderon once more.
Deliver the arcane epistle to Baderon in Limsa Lominsa.
<Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,1)/>. Considering your role in events thus far, there are few others to whom I would entrust this task.
Ahtzapfyn, the pirate behind the attempted destruction of the <Emphasis>Victory</Emphasis>, was in possession of a curious missive.
This missive was penned in the most unusual lettering─a script that we believe to be some manner of code.
And despite the likelihood of the message containing secrets of vital interest to the Maelstrom, there are none among us who can read it.
In cases such as this, I am told the Yellowjackets are wont to turn to Baderon and his convenient...connections.
Thus I would have you deliver this missive in person to the proprietor of the Drowning Wench. Into his hand, and no other, do you understand?
Ahoy there, <Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,1)/>. I 'ear ye made quite a name fer yerself at the Drydocks.

Ahtbyrm laid out the entire tale fer me. The poor bastard was reelin' at 'is old man's part in the deed, but at least ye kept the <Emphasis>Victory</Emphasis> from bein' blown into a mess o' slag and splinters.
And fer that, I give ye me own thanks as well!
Ye've made a niche for yerself 'ere in Limsa, and I 'ope from 'ere on in, ye can─
Eh? This time ye've got a task fer <Emphasis>me</Emphasis>, ye say?
Yer needin' a bloke what can untangle some funny letters? Now what kind o' letters might these be? Let's see this missive of yers.
I reckon I can find ye a canny bastard to read this fer ye. Ugly sod by the name o' Baderon.
Ye know, I feel like yer one o' me regulars now, <Split(<Highlight>ObjectParameter(1)</Highlight>, ,1)/>.
Ye've shown guts, and, Navigator 'elp me, I believe I can trust ye.
Ghimthota was right about this message bein' somethin' important─we've got us some trouble brewin', and no mistake. Get yer kit together and I'll explain.
